content:
Enable Previews for All Assets

Make it easier for users to browse analytics assets in collections. Replace generic icons with preview thumbnails of your CRM Analytics contents and Lightning reports and dashboards, including those that have row-level security restrictions.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

From Setup, enter Analytics in the Quick Find box, then select Settings.
Select Show preview thumbnails for secure lenses and dashboards.
Click Save.

Important: Even if row-level security applies to the dataset used by a lens or dashboard, the preview thumbnail could expose data from restricted rows.

To enable previews for Lightning assets:
From Setup, enter Reports in the Quick Find box, then select Reports and Dashboards Settings.
Select Show preview thumbnails for reports and Lightning dashboards.
Click Save.
title: Enabling Asset Previews in Salesforce
